{"id":"0911.0857","submitter":"Ralph Gelderen van","authors":"Ralph van Gelderen and C. Morais Smith","title":"Rashba and intrinsic spin-orbit interactions in biased bilayer graphene","comments":"10 pages, 10 figures","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. B 81, 125435 (2010)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevB.81.125435","report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.mes-hall","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We investigate the effect that the intrinsic spin-orbit and the inter- and\nintra-layer Rashba interactions have on the energy spectrum of either an\nunbiased or a biased graphene bilayer. We find that under certain conditions, a\nDirac cone is formed out of a parabolic band and that it is possible to create\na \"Mexican hat\"-like energy dispersion in an unbiased bilayer. In addition, in\nthe presence of only an intralayer Rashba interaction, the K (K') point splits\ninto four distinct ones, contrarily to the case in single-layer graphene, where\nthe splitting also takes place, but the low-energy dispersion at these points\nremains identical.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 4 Nov 2009 15:48:48 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 5 Nov 2009 11:39:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2010-04-01"}
